HEADWORD: Neurility
<hw>Neu*ril"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ney^ron</grk> nerve.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The special
properties and functions of the nerves; that capacity for transmitting a
stimulus which belongs to nerves.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark>
